element.name: pxnum
element.description: Optional Pricing Number

element.name: intervalHasSeconds
element.description: flag that indicates that value of interval is in seconds

element.name: dateTimeInfo
element.description: choice of setting start end datetime or list start datetimes and duration

element.name: intervalHasSeconds
element.description: flag that indicates that value of interval is in seconds

element.name: adjustmentNormal
element.description: Adjust historical pricing to reflect: Regular Cash, Interim, 1st Interim, 2nd Interim, 3rd Interim, 4th Interim, 5th Interim, Income, Estimated, Partnership Distribution, Final, Interest on Capital, Distribution, Prorated.

element.name: adjustmentAbnormal
element.description: Adjust historical pricing to reflect: Special Cash, Liquidation, Capital Gains, Long-Term Capital Gains, Short-Term Capital Gains, Memorial, Return of Capital, Rights Redemption, Miscellaneous, Return Premium, Preferred Rights Redemption, Proceeds/Rights, Proceeds/Shares, Proceeds/Warrants.

element.name: adjustmentSplit
element.description: Adjust historical pricing and/or volume to reflect: Spin-Offs, Stock Splits/Consolidations, Stock Dividend/Bonus, Rights Offerings/Entitlement.

element.name: adjustmentFollowDPDF
element.description: Adjust historical pricing and/or volume as per user's DPDF screen

element.name: includeClientSpecificFields
element.description: option to retrieve custom fields for new XDF source for currency trades: ClientDomicile ClientSegment ClientSubsegment ClientIdentifier Direction TradeId

element.name: includeTradeId
element.description: option to retrieve unique identifier for a trade event.

element.name: filter
element.description: format example: "size>10 && cc=ob"

element.name: includeTradeDate
element.description: option to retrieve the date of the trade.

element.name: includeDirtyTicks
element.description: option to retrieve ticks that had been subsequently cancelled or amended. Return cancelledFlag, correctionFlag, and nativeTradeId.

element.name: includeSubSecondTimestamps
element.description: option to retrieve sub-second timestamps - where available

element.name: includeBloombergStandardConditionCodes
element.description: option to retrieve the Bloomberg Standard Condition Codes. Return bloombergStandardConditionCodes.

element.name: includeMarketModelTypology
element.description: option to retrieve the Market Model Typology trade type, where available. Return marketModelTypology.

element.name: includeNativeTradeId
element.description: option to retrieve he Trade Aggressor. Return tradeAggressor.

element.name: includeAggressor
element.description: option to the Market Model Typology trade type, where available. Return marketModelTypology.

element.name: includeSecurityStatusEvents
element.description: option to retrieve trading phase, suspension status and auction status changes. Return tradingPhase, suspensionState, auctionState and simplifiedState.

element.name: includeESMATradeFlag
element.description: option to retrieve ESMA Trade flag. Return ESMATradeFlag

element.name: filters
element.description: define intraday tick request FDM filter.

element.name: filterName
element.description: name of the filter: have to be unique, e.g. "filter_0"

element.name: fieldId
element.description: ticker plant FDM field ID string:e.g. "EVENT_PRICE"

element.name: filterRule
element.description: rule apply on this field: e.g. "[10.5, 11.5]"

element.name: dateTimeRange
element.description: provides start/end datetime

element.name: startDateDuration
element.description: provides array of start datetime and duration for every day
